18/02/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Thursday (February 18th) that they conducted a controlled detonation of a homemade bomb planted outside the office of Citizen Protection Minister Mihalis Chrysohoidis. The blast, late Wednesday, caused minor damage but no injuries. Police arrived after being told of a suspicious package outside the office. No group has claimed responsibility yet. On Tuesday, a bomb exploded at an Athens office of the US financial company JP Morgan, causing damage but no injuries. (AP, Reuters, RIA-Novosti, ANA-MPA - 18/02/10)
